1
00:00:04,809 --> 00:00:07,412
When will you catch that guy for me?

2
00:00:07,479 --> 00:00:10,448
Why did my mom and dad die?

3
00:00:10,515 --> 00:00:12,851
The man who was interviewing
our dad is Yuji Tsuda.

4
00:00:12,917 --> 00:00:14,219
-Just let me hear your side.
-I'm busy.

5
00:00:14,285 --> 00:00:17,422
-He won a newcomer award in university.
-I'll come by again tonight.

6
00:00:17,489 --> 00:00:20,125
Right after the incident,
Tsuda disappeared.

7
00:00:20,191 --> 00:00:21,926
He fled because he's the killer?

8
00:00:21,993 --> 00:00:23,428
What are you going to do?

9
00:00:23,995 --> 00:00:25,163
What will you do…

10
00:00:25,230 --> 00:00:26,764
if you find Tsuda?

11
00:00:29,534 --> 00:00:32,837
He was brought in this morning.
He didn't have an ID, but said his name.

12
00:00:32,904 --> 00:00:33,872
Is it really Tsuda?

13
00:00:33,938 --> 00:00:35,306
There's no way I would mistake him.

14
00:00:35,373 --> 00:00:36,341
But…

15
00:00:37,609 --> 00:00:39,777
Pancreatic cancer, stage four.

16
00:00:39,844 --> 00:00:42,046
He went into septic shock…

17
00:00:42,947 --> 00:00:44,382
and is now in a coma.

18
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:51,823
The cancer has metastasized
to the liver and lungs.

19
00:00:51,890 --> 00:00:53,625
He has about six months to live.

20
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,326
About this patient--

21
00:00:55,393 --> 00:00:57,228
He wasn't receiving treatment.

22
00:00:59,030 --> 00:01:02,734
There are no signs he ever had
standard treatment, such as surgery.

23
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:05,803
He likely had reasons
he couldn't go to a hospital.

24
00:01:05,870 --> 00:01:07,005
His injuries may be from--

25
00:01:07,071 --> 00:01:08,540
I don't care.

26
00:01:12,677 --> 00:01:14,379
Will he regain consciousness?

27
00:01:16,114 --> 00:01:20,051
Currently, we are using vasopressors
to maintain his blood pressure,

28
00:01:20,652 --> 00:01:22,220
but the situation is very grim.

29
00:01:29,661 --> 00:01:32,297
Is it possible he might never wake up?

30
00:01:35,967 --> 00:01:37,735
Don't screw with me.

31
00:01:44,409 --> 00:01:45,677
Another case?

32
00:01:55,486 --> 00:01:56,521
Hello?

33
00:01:59,824 --> 00:02:02,460
There's a suspected arson-murder
in Kanagawa Ward.

34
00:02:02,527 --> 00:02:03,695
Let's go.

35
00:02:03,761 --> 00:02:05,196
Who cares about that?

36
00:02:07,899 --> 00:02:10,702
-This isn't an investigation!
-So what?

37
00:02:10,768 --> 00:02:12,804
They will notice detectives
hanging around.

38
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:14,806
We won't be able to get close to Tsuda!

39
00:02:18,409 --> 00:02:19,577
In that case,

40
00:02:21,713 --> 00:02:23,248
we'll do it before then.

41
00:02:24,749 --> 00:02:25,583
Makoto…

42
00:02:25,650 --> 00:02:28,286
We can't let a disease kill him!

43
00:02:31,389 --> 00:02:33,291
The possibility isn't zero yet.

44
00:02:34,359 --> 00:02:36,828
If the antibiotics and vasopressors work,

45
00:02:36,894 --> 00:02:39,030
there's a chance
he'll regain consciousness.

46
00:02:39,530 --> 00:02:41,566
Even if Tsuda isn't long for the world,

47
00:02:42,533 --> 00:02:45,169
it's enough time to find out his motive.

48
00:02:47,905 --> 00:02:49,173
It's ironic, but…

49
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:53,177
right now, we've no choice
but to believe in him.

50
00:03:10,695 --> 00:03:12,196
Around 10:30 p.m.,

51
00:03:12,263 --> 00:03:16,100
following a report from a passerby,
we discovered an apartment fire.

52
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:17,935
The other residents evacuated,

53
00:03:18,002 --> 00:03:21,239
but the resident of the room
where the fire broke out, Aiko Mizusawa,

54
00:03:21,306 --> 00:03:23,608
was taken to the hospital
and pronounced dead.

55
00:03:25,610 --> 00:03:27,879
Firefighters said it started
at the entrance.

56
00:03:27,945 --> 00:03:30,782
It seems a burning object was pushed in
through the mail slot.

57
00:03:32,417 --> 00:03:33,685
Wait, Mr. Tagusari.

58
00:03:50,435 --> 00:03:51,536
Hello.

59
00:03:51,602 --> 00:03:52,770
Hello.

60
00:03:52,837 --> 00:03:54,839
Make no mistake, it was arson and murder.

61
00:03:54,906 --> 00:03:57,108
And she was so young too.

62
00:03:57,809 --> 00:04:01,279
Still, it's the second floor.
She could've escaped through the window.

63
00:04:01,346 --> 00:04:05,383
From the condition of the bathroom,
it's likely she had just finished bathing.

64
00:04:05,950 --> 00:04:08,619
Then, a flyer was set on fire
and thrown in.

65
00:04:08,686 --> 00:04:10,788
It ignited a spray can
left at the entrance

66
00:04:10,855 --> 00:04:11,989
and caused it to burst.

67
00:04:12,056 --> 00:04:14,892
From there, the fire seems
to have spread rapidly.

68
00:04:15,993 --> 00:04:17,895
-Let's film the onlookers.
-Onlookers?

69
00:04:18,463 --> 00:04:19,731
Nosy folks.

70
00:04:19,797 --> 00:04:20,798
Oh, right.

71
00:04:22,467 --> 00:04:23,401
Right.

72
00:04:26,671 --> 00:04:28,373
Quite a crowd has gathered.

73
00:04:28,439 --> 00:04:30,775
Probably filming
for social media or something.

74
00:04:30,842 --> 00:04:31,676
Ishizaka.

75
00:04:31,743 --> 00:04:33,745
Face this way. You're looking too much.

76
00:04:33,811 --> 00:04:35,113
-A bit to the right.
-Okay.

77
00:04:35,179 --> 00:04:36,080
Yes, right there.

78
00:04:36,147 --> 00:04:38,216
Mr. Tagusari, you take photos too.

79
00:04:40,451 --> 00:04:41,886
Hey, are you listening?

80
00:04:42,687 --> 00:04:46,057
Arsonists sometimes return
to the scene, you know.

81
00:04:46,758 --> 00:04:48,259
They're probably gone by now.

82
00:04:50,495 --> 00:04:52,997
Those kinds of people just
want to see things burning.

83
00:04:56,901 --> 00:04:59,871
Wait, don't take photos so blatantly.

84
00:05:12,016 --> 00:05:13,851
Something is stuck here.

85
00:05:13,918 --> 00:05:16,220
Is it a fragment of something?

86
00:05:19,991 --> 00:05:21,859
Ms. Kiritani, send this to forensics.

87
00:05:21,926 --> 00:05:22,827
Yes, sir.

88
00:05:25,196 --> 00:05:26,998
Please pay attention.

89
00:05:27,498 --> 00:05:28,433
Okay.

90
00:05:28,499 --> 00:05:31,602
The cause of death
was carbon monoxide poisoning?

91
00:05:31,669 --> 00:05:34,972
She inhaled the smoke
that filled the room.

92
00:05:35,039 --> 00:05:39,310
Why didn't she notice
a burning flyer being thrown

93
00:05:39,377 --> 00:05:40,778
into the mail slot?

94
00:05:41,312 --> 00:05:44,115
It seems she was using
a hair dryer after her shower.

95
00:05:44,182 --> 00:05:45,183
I see.

96
00:05:48,686 --> 00:05:50,755
Did you lose big at the races?

97
00:05:51,489 --> 00:05:52,390
What?

98
00:05:52,457 --> 00:05:55,560
Since yesterday, you've been
even more unmotivated than usual.

99
00:06:08,105 --> 00:06:09,106
What's wrong?

100
00:06:12,677 --> 00:06:13,845
Please go on ahead.

101
00:06:40,805 --> 00:06:42,840
-Tell us.
-I have nothing to say.

102
00:06:42,907 --> 00:06:45,576
I'll come by again tonight.

103
00:07:02,026 --> 00:07:04,128
You two aren't alike at all, are you?

104
00:07:05,897 --> 00:07:08,366
I can't believe
you're both in the police force.

105
00:07:09,634 --> 00:07:10,535
Both?

106
00:07:13,337 --> 00:07:15,806
Why didn't you become
a forensic scientist?

107
00:07:17,808 --> 00:07:19,477
With that much knowledge,

108
00:07:19,544 --> 00:07:22,079
it wouldn't be strange for you
to follow that path.

109
00:07:25,249 --> 00:07:27,151
That was my intention, a long time ago.

110
00:07:27,218 --> 00:07:28,719
Then why the police?

111
00:07:31,822 --> 00:07:32,657
Oh!

112
00:07:32,723 --> 00:07:33,791
Mr. Tagusari!

113
00:07:33,858 --> 00:07:36,460
I brought the autopsy report.

114
00:07:41,299 --> 00:07:43,568
-Oh, excuse me.
-Goodbye.

115
00:07:46,637 --> 00:07:50,241
The body found in the apartment
was identified by her driver's license

116
00:07:50,308 --> 00:07:51,876
as resident Aiko Mizusawa, 20 years old.

117
00:07:51,943 --> 00:07:54,178
She worked part-time at a food factory.

118
00:07:54,245 --> 00:07:57,081
However, we haven't looked into
her relationships yet.

119
00:07:57,915 --> 00:07:59,517
Are her parents far away?

120
00:08:00,418 --> 00:08:03,120
Her family home is in Akita,

121
00:08:03,187 --> 00:08:05,690
but her father is serving time
for fraud and assault,

122
00:08:05,756 --> 00:08:07,191
and her mother is deceased.

123
00:08:08,326 --> 00:08:12,597
After her father's arrest,
she was taken into a foster home,

124
00:08:12,663 --> 00:08:14,765
so it seems she's estranged
from relatives.

125
00:08:15,466 --> 00:08:16,634
Any witnesses?

126
00:08:17,268 --> 00:08:18,703
None have come up so far.

127
00:08:18,769 --> 00:08:21,339
No security cameras were installed
in the apartment.

128
00:08:21,405 --> 00:08:23,107
Please report the autopsy results.

129
00:08:23,608 --> 00:08:25,943
The cause of death
is carbon monoxide poisoning.

130
00:08:26,010 --> 00:08:30,414
No sleeping pills were detected,
and no signs of a struggle were found.

131
00:08:30,481 --> 00:08:31,983
Is there anything else?

132
00:08:32,049 --> 00:08:32,950
Nothing.

133
00:08:37,188 --> 00:08:39,957
Her father is in prison, huh?

134
00:08:40,024 --> 00:08:42,226
Her life must have been tough.

135
00:08:50,401 --> 00:08:52,436
Don't go off on your own again.

136
00:08:54,505 --> 00:08:55,673
I'll be careful.

137
00:09:03,481 --> 00:09:07,318
If Tsuda's condition changes,
the hospital will contact us immediately.

138
00:09:07,885 --> 00:09:09,920
Until then, don't act on your own.

139
00:09:20,798 --> 00:09:21,866
I know.

140
00:09:24,869 --> 00:09:29,640
Ms. Mizusawa started working here
about a year ago, I think.

141
00:09:30,241 --> 00:09:33,177
Did you hear anything
about her having any troubles?

142
00:09:33,244 --> 00:09:34,612
No, nothing.

143
00:09:35,413 --> 00:09:37,014
Any employees she's close with?

144
00:09:37,782 --> 00:09:38,716
None.

145
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:43,020
That girl was unsociable
and only spoke about work.

146
00:09:49,326 --> 00:09:50,761
Oh, I have to go.

147
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:54,699
She sounds like you, Mr. Tagusari.

148
00:09:55,733 --> 00:09:58,736
Aiko Mizusawa also lacked social skills,

149
00:09:58,803 --> 00:10:01,138
so finding any relationships
might be difficult.

150
00:10:02,239 --> 00:10:03,340
Don't liken me to her.

151
00:10:04,809 --> 00:10:06,043
So you do have friends?

152
00:10:11,382 --> 00:10:12,283
Minoru.

153
00:10:13,984 --> 00:10:15,319
He's your brother!

154
00:10:16,253 --> 00:10:17,154
Yes.

155
00:10:22,460 --> 00:10:23,561
Yes, this is Kudo.

156
00:10:23,627 --> 00:10:27,798
From Aiko Mizusawa's smartphone, we found
the person she contacted before she died.

157
00:10:27,865 --> 00:10:29,667
A woman named Saki Yokokura.

158
00:10:29,734 --> 00:10:32,903
We're helping First Division
look for witnesses. Look into this.

159
00:10:38,809 --> 00:10:40,845
I'm Kudo from the Aoi Station.

160
00:10:40,911 --> 00:10:43,547
What do the police need from me?

161
00:10:43,614 --> 00:10:46,183
You know Aiko Mizusawa, don't you?

162
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:47,418
Yes.

163
00:10:47,485 --> 00:10:51,055
Excuse me, but what was your relationship
with her?

164
00:10:52,123 --> 00:10:53,591
We're friends.

165
00:10:54,291 --> 00:10:56,460
Did something happen to Aiko?

166
00:10:57,762 --> 00:10:59,230
She died in a fire.

167
00:10:59,296 --> 00:11:00,264
What?

168
00:11:01,699 --> 00:11:05,503
Before she died,
it seems she contacted you.

169
00:11:09,340 --> 00:11:11,976
What were you doing yesterday
around 10:30 p.m.?

170
00:11:12,042 --> 00:11:14,912
I was working overtime.

171
00:11:16,380 --> 00:11:17,681
Please wait a moment.

172
00:11:19,984 --> 00:11:21,085
Excuse me.

173
00:11:22,086 --> 00:11:24,021
You can check with my company.

174
00:11:24,088 --> 00:11:25,389
Thank you.

175
00:11:26,290 --> 00:11:27,858
And one more thing.

176
00:11:28,726 --> 00:11:31,896
The last message Ms. Mizusawa sent you

177
00:11:31,962 --> 00:11:34,298
mentioned wanting to talk
about this "Togo" person.

178
00:11:34,365 --> 00:11:35,699
What does this mean?

179
00:11:39,603 --> 00:11:41,238
Do you know something?

180
00:11:41,305 --> 00:11:43,908
I don't know the details,

181
00:11:45,276 --> 00:11:47,344
but Aiko said

182
00:11:48,145 --> 00:11:51,448
she was being stalked by this man.

183
00:11:55,252 --> 00:11:56,287
Hey, Mr. Tagusari!

184
00:11:58,222 --> 00:12:00,357
Thank goodness, I made it in time.

185
00:12:01,292 --> 00:12:05,296
Forensics sent us the results for the
substance found under her nails.

186
00:12:05,362 --> 00:12:06,630
Thank you.

187
00:12:07,264 --> 00:12:09,366
-See you later.
-See you.

188
00:12:10,267 --> 00:12:14,171
AUTOPSY REPORT

189
00:12:20,611 --> 00:12:21,912
Did the hospital call?

190
00:12:21,979 --> 00:12:22,980
No.

191
00:12:24,315 --> 00:12:25,382
Still investigating?

192
00:12:26,617 --> 00:12:27,918
It wrapped up just now.

193
00:12:29,954 --> 00:12:31,222
I'm going for a drink.

194
00:12:31,288 --> 00:12:33,190
I can't sleep if I go home anyway.

195
00:12:33,858 --> 00:12:36,193
In that case, come with me for a bit.

196
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:44,969
We're heading to the crime scene?

197
00:12:46,103 --> 00:12:48,105
Forensics sent back Aiko Mizusawa--

198
00:12:48,172 --> 00:12:49,039
Listen!

199
00:12:50,674 --> 00:12:53,644
What was found under her fingernails
was rush grass.

200
00:12:54,278 --> 00:12:55,179
Rush grass?

201
00:12:55,679 --> 00:12:57,882
If it's in the room,
it must be the tatami mats.

202
00:12:59,583 --> 00:13:01,719
Must have clawed them
when she couldn't breathe.

203
00:13:01,785 --> 00:13:03,254
Why not open the window?

204
00:13:05,990 --> 00:13:08,392
It's not that Aiko Mizusawa
couldn't escape.

205
00:13:11,862 --> 00:13:13,931
Is there a reason she didn't run?

206
00:13:16,934 --> 00:13:19,303
-Hello.
-Hello.

207
00:13:23,874 --> 00:13:26,677
She passed away here, so…

208
00:13:27,478 --> 00:13:29,914
The rush grass must be
from these tatami mats.

209
00:13:38,622 --> 00:13:39,523
What's wrong?

210
00:13:40,457 --> 00:13:42,726
Someone moved the bed recently.

211
00:13:44,662 --> 00:13:45,863
Wait, hold that side.

212
00:13:45,930 --> 00:13:46,764
Sure.

213
00:13:51,001 --> 00:13:52,503
It's heavy!

214
00:13:52,569 --> 00:13:54,371
Were tatami mats always this heavy?

215
00:13:54,438 --> 00:13:56,674
I don't often carry tatami mats around…

216
00:13:58,709 --> 00:13:59,643
Don't you remember?

217
00:14:00,477 --> 00:14:01,745
Remember what?

218
00:14:01,812 --> 00:14:05,883
Back in the day, you made a fuss,
saying you saw a tiny samurai at home.

219
00:14:06,517 --> 00:14:09,853
We lifted up the tatami
because you said he escaped into the gap.

220
00:14:12,456 --> 00:14:14,325
A tiny samurai?

221
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:17,261
Never mind.

222
00:14:20,831 --> 00:14:22,333
Oh, it's budging!

223
00:14:22,399 --> 00:14:23,801
Lift it!

224
00:14:23,867 --> 00:14:25,936
And push!

225
00:14:26,003 --> 00:14:27,271
Whew.

226
00:14:46,056 --> 00:14:48,225
Gold bars were found
under this tatami mat,

227
00:14:48,292 --> 00:14:49,660
and are being inspected.

228
00:14:49,727 --> 00:14:52,296
If you go to the scene,
at least let me know.

229
00:14:52,363 --> 00:14:54,331
I didn't intend to investigate.

230
00:14:54,398 --> 00:14:58,202
I was the one who asked.
I wanted to see the scene once more.

231
00:14:58,268 --> 00:14:59,370
I'm sorry.

232
00:15:02,473 --> 00:15:04,341
Report the situation.

233
00:15:13,751 --> 00:15:17,488
If the gold bars are real,
they're worth about 100 million yen.

234
00:15:17,554 --> 00:15:18,822
One hundred million?

235
00:15:18,889 --> 00:15:21,358
Aiko Mizusawa gave up
on putting out the fire,

236
00:15:21,425 --> 00:15:24,228
and tried to move the bed to take
the gold from under it.

237
00:15:24,294 --> 00:15:28,265
But before she could,
she died from carbon monoxide poisoning.

238
00:15:28,332 --> 00:15:30,868
But Aiko Mizusawa was only 20 years old.

239
00:15:31,368 --> 00:15:32,669
So many gold bars…

240
00:15:32,736 --> 00:15:35,272
Maybe her father got them through fraud.

241
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:39,343
Cross-check the gold bars
with theft reports.

242
00:15:39,410 --> 00:15:40,310
Yes, sir!

243
00:15:42,579 --> 00:15:46,250
She was being stalked by a man
named Togo, wasn't she?

244
00:15:46,784 --> 00:15:50,254
Maybe he was after those gold bars.

245
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,622
Mr. Hyuga.

246
00:15:51,688 --> 00:15:53,290
Any info about Togo?

247
00:15:53,357 --> 00:15:55,192
We didn't get any information at all.

248
00:15:55,793 --> 00:15:58,062
His relationship with her is also unknown.

249
00:15:58,662 --> 00:16:01,165
Who on earth is this Togo?

250
00:16:01,231 --> 00:16:04,234
We might find their connection
through the gold bars.

251
00:16:04,902 --> 00:16:08,472
Until the results come back, let's check
Mizusawa's relationships again.

252
00:16:30,661 --> 00:16:31,929
Haruko.

253
00:16:31,995 --> 00:16:33,097
Have a moment?

254
00:16:34,398 --> 00:16:35,532
I'm busy right now.

255
00:16:35,599 --> 00:16:36,934
Come on. Just this once.

256
00:16:38,469 --> 00:16:41,772
-I've heard that about 100 times already.
-Then this is the 101st.

257
00:16:45,042 --> 00:16:46,577
Oh, how rare.

258
00:16:46,643 --> 00:16:48,378
You're with a girl today?

259
00:16:48,445 --> 00:16:49,513
What?

260
00:16:52,883 --> 00:16:54,418
Kudo, why are you here?

261
00:16:56,553 --> 00:17:00,023
If you keep acting on your own,
it will affect my evaluation too.

262
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:03,026
Only terrible men
mistreat ladies, you know.

263
00:17:05,195 --> 00:17:06,396
Do whatever you want.

264
00:17:09,666 --> 00:17:12,202
Find a man named Togo,
who was stalking this woman.

265
00:17:13,570 --> 00:17:14,671
Togo?

266
00:17:14,738 --> 00:17:16,507
Which is it, really?

267
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,809
Not sure if you're motivated or not…

268
00:17:20,344 --> 00:17:21,845
I'm just a little curious.

269
00:17:22,546 --> 00:17:24,982
-Who is this woman?
-Her name is Aiko Mizusawa.

270
00:17:25,048 --> 00:17:27,918
-She had 100 million in gold at her home.
-Hey!

271
00:17:28,752 --> 00:17:30,621
Don't leak that info to a civilian!

272
00:17:31,455 --> 00:17:34,424
I'll give you cash,
so go out and buy some Big Katsu.

273
00:17:34,491 --> 00:17:35,425
What?

274
00:17:35,492 --> 00:17:37,561
What you're doing will get us in trouble.

275
00:17:38,162 --> 00:17:39,796
Only if you tell someone.

276
00:17:41,732 --> 00:17:43,567
It's just getting good.

277
00:17:43,634 --> 00:17:46,003
Can you hurry and let me continue reading?

278
00:17:47,237 --> 00:17:48,906
Who is that person?

279
00:17:51,475 --> 00:17:54,111
What is your relationship with Ms. Haruko?

280
00:17:55,145 --> 00:17:56,246
Just an acquaintance.

281
00:17:56,313 --> 00:17:58,715
Your range of "acquaintance"
is quite broad, huh.

282
00:18:04,254 --> 00:18:06,423
I'm kind of hungry.

283
00:18:07,191 --> 00:18:09,026
Want some ramen before going home?

284
00:18:09,893 --> 00:18:10,794
Just us?

285
00:18:10,861 --> 00:18:12,963
Sure. I don't see anyone else here.

286
00:18:15,399 --> 00:18:18,569
Since you came to our station,
we've never gone for lunch.

287
00:18:18,635 --> 00:18:19,870
So let's hang out.

288
00:18:26,376 --> 00:18:28,178
You really need to think that hard?

289
00:18:29,446 --> 00:18:30,280
Well…

290
00:18:31,248 --> 00:18:32,549
-Let's go!
-Next time.

291
00:18:42,626 --> 00:18:44,661
I'll order a big one. That will show him…

292
00:18:47,998 --> 00:18:51,735
PREMIUM MILK

293
00:18:53,604 --> 00:18:54,671
Welcome.

294
00:18:59,042 --> 00:19:00,344
You're playing that again.

295
00:19:02,646 --> 00:19:03,880
Starving, aren't you?

296
00:19:03,947 --> 00:19:05,048
Shut up.

297
00:19:06,650 --> 00:19:07,618
Just got off work?

298
00:19:07,684 --> 00:19:09,753
There was an autopsy at Yomogida Station.

299
00:19:10,254 --> 00:19:11,421
Get me the same one.

300
00:19:11,488 --> 00:19:12,389
All right.

301
00:19:14,958 --> 00:19:16,526
What happened to the gold bars?

302
00:19:17,694 --> 00:19:19,730
We should know the origin soon.

303
00:19:21,498 --> 00:19:24,401
Why would she have gold bars…

304
00:19:24,468 --> 00:19:25,502
Who knows?

305
00:19:25,569 --> 00:19:27,804
But it has nothing to do with her father.

306
00:19:27,871 --> 00:19:28,939
Why?

307
00:19:29,006 --> 00:19:31,441
Her father went to prison 13 years ago.

308
00:19:31,508 --> 00:19:33,644
At that time,
Aiko Mizusawa was only seven.

309
00:19:33,710 --> 00:19:34,811
Oh, right.

310
00:19:35,479 --> 00:19:38,348
You wouldn't entrust 100 million
in gold bars to a child.

311
00:19:38,415 --> 00:19:39,249
Right.

312
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:42,352
You guys talking about treasure?

313
00:19:43,387 --> 00:19:44,988
Come on, tell me. Where is it?

314
00:19:45,555 --> 00:19:46,623
The scene of a fire.

315
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:52,529
It was at an apartment in Kanagawa Ward.

316
00:19:55,032 --> 00:19:56,433
I hate fires.

317
00:19:59,603 --> 00:20:01,505
1995, APRIL 26

318
00:20:02,639 --> 00:20:05,375
Oh, today is the day
you cook for the whole week, right?

319
00:20:05,442 --> 00:20:06,643
Oh, yes.

320
00:20:06,710 --> 00:20:08,612
How is Ms. Fumi's leg?

321
00:20:09,179 --> 00:20:11,381
Not very good, it seems.

322
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:16,253
They say it will probably require surgery.

323
00:20:16,820 --> 00:20:19,489
Accidents in the mountains
are scary, aren't they?

324
00:20:19,556 --> 00:20:22,359
Anyway, I'll go prepare this week's meals.

325
00:20:22,426 --> 00:20:23,493
Okay.

326
00:20:28,999 --> 00:20:30,801
KOJIMA GOLD FACTORY

327
00:20:32,302 --> 00:20:34,338
Let me know if you need anything.

328
00:20:34,404 --> 00:20:37,574
I'm sorry, Mogi.
I can't do anything by myself.

329
00:20:37,641 --> 00:20:38,475
It's okay.

330
00:20:38,542 --> 00:20:39,810
I'll borrow your kitchen.

331
00:20:39,876 --> 00:20:40,711
Sure.

332
00:20:50,854 --> 00:20:51,855
Paramedics!

333
00:20:51,922 --> 00:20:52,889
Over here!

334
00:20:54,057 --> 00:20:58,195
-Male victim, possible airway injury!
-Paramedics!

335
00:20:59,129 --> 00:21:00,097
Darling!

336
00:21:00,163 --> 00:21:01,231
In the factory…

337
00:21:01,298 --> 00:21:02,566
There is another…

338
00:21:02,632 --> 00:21:05,268
-Possible victim in the factory!
-The factory!

339
00:21:05,836 --> 00:21:07,571
-Prepare to reenter!
-Roger!

340
00:21:07,637 --> 00:21:08,605
Roger!

341
00:21:09,306 --> 00:21:10,741
Anyone in there?

342
00:21:10,807 --> 00:21:12,209
Can you hear me?

343
00:21:12,776 --> 00:21:14,511
-Anyone in there?
-Anyone in there?

344
00:21:15,312 --> 00:21:16,513
Anyone there?

345
00:21:18,081 --> 00:21:19,049
Found the victim!

346
00:21:19,616 --> 00:21:21,785
-Are you okay?
-Can you hear me?

347
00:21:21,852 --> 00:21:22,919
Let's move him!

348
00:21:22,986 --> 00:21:25,122
Okay. One, two, three!

349
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,168
Just forget about it already.

350
00:21:40,971 --> 00:21:42,873
Things will soon be over.

351
00:21:44,674 --> 00:21:45,609
Over?

352
00:21:47,177 --> 00:21:48,678
They found Tsuda.

353
00:21:50,447 --> 00:21:51,581
What?

354
00:22:19,176 --> 00:22:21,645
You can't bribe me
with dumplings, you know.

355
00:22:22,179 --> 00:22:23,113
I see.

356
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:24,948
Mogi's are excellent, though.

357
00:22:27,918 --> 00:22:28,919
Minoru?

358
00:22:29,786 --> 00:22:31,154
Is this really a pawnshop?

359
00:22:32,155 --> 00:22:33,723
Want to try pawning something?

360
00:22:33,790 --> 00:22:34,724
What?

361
00:22:35,592 --> 00:22:37,594
I will buy anything you've got.

362
00:22:37,661 --> 00:22:39,095
No, thanks.

363
00:22:47,471 --> 00:22:48,805
What brings you here today?

364
00:22:49,706 --> 00:22:52,275
I figured Makoto probably didn't tell you.

365
00:22:52,809 --> 00:22:53,810
What?

366
00:22:53,877 --> 00:22:55,412
I ought to tell you, Haruko.

367
00:22:55,979 --> 00:22:56,913
Tell me?

368
00:22:59,783 --> 00:23:03,587
Tsuda is currently
hospitalized at Shosen Medical University.

369
00:23:05,455 --> 00:23:08,158
I don't know why
he came back here, though.

370
00:23:11,728 --> 00:23:12,929
Haruko, you…

371
00:23:14,931 --> 00:23:16,399
You really took care of us.

372
00:23:19,202 --> 00:23:21,171
You spoke to us back then.

373
00:23:23,607 --> 00:23:24,908
What's wrong?

374
00:23:26,142 --> 00:23:29,012
Where are my mom and dad?

375
00:23:30,647 --> 00:23:32,215
Where are they?

376
00:23:36,286 --> 00:23:39,422
Now, it is time for the final farewell.

377
00:23:43,426 --> 00:23:44,628
Minoru…

378
00:23:44,694 --> 00:23:45,929
Both of us…

379
00:23:46,496 --> 00:23:48,598
were able to see our parents
one last time.

380
00:23:51,167 --> 00:23:52,569
Since then,

381
00:23:54,471 --> 00:23:56,106
you've always stayed by our side.

382
00:23:57,841 --> 00:24:01,645
Happy birthday to you

383
00:24:01,711 --> 00:24:05,048
Happy birthday to you

384
00:24:05,682 --> 00:24:08,451
Happy birthday dear

385
00:24:08,518 --> 00:24:09,853
Minoru!

386
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:11,555
1996

387
00:24:17,227 --> 00:24:19,996
You even helped us look for Tsuda.

388
00:24:22,299 --> 00:24:23,433
We…

389
00:24:24,501 --> 00:24:26,469
took up so much of your time, Haruko.

390
00:24:28,338 --> 00:24:29,406
Minoru…

391
00:24:31,541 --> 00:24:32,475
I'm sorry.

392
00:24:35,045 --> 00:24:36,980
Why are you saying that now?

393
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:40,784
That guy left me scarred too.

394
00:24:45,255 --> 00:24:47,757
Well, I'm going back to work.

395
00:24:47,824 --> 00:24:50,093
Eat the gyoza while they're hot, okay?

396
00:24:51,261 --> 00:24:52,929
Is this your final job?

397
00:24:57,667 --> 00:24:59,336
Is there no other way?

398
00:25:06,409 --> 00:25:08,411
You should visit Mogi sometimes.

399
00:25:09,212 --> 00:25:10,814
I'm sure he'll be lonely.

400
00:25:32,602 --> 00:25:33,803
A year ago,

401
00:25:33,870 --> 00:25:37,540
there was a robbery of 400 million yen
in gold bars in Akita Prefecture.

402
00:25:38,041 --> 00:25:40,176
The gold bars stolen then

403
00:25:40,744 --> 00:25:44,214
match the ones found
in Aiko Mizusawa's home.

404
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,149
What do we know about this robbery?

405
00:25:46,816 --> 00:25:48,852
One of the four robbers

406
00:25:48,918 --> 00:25:51,321
had a tattoo on the side
of his neck. Just that.

407
00:25:51,388 --> 00:25:52,455
However…

408
00:25:52,522 --> 00:25:56,159
It's highly possible that Mizusawa
was also a member.

409
00:25:56,226 --> 00:25:59,029
We assumed that this crime
was committed by people

410
00:25:59,095 --> 00:26:02,332
lured by a shady part-time-job posting
on social media.

411
00:26:02,399 --> 00:26:04,000
It's believed a criminal group,

412
00:26:04,067 --> 00:26:06,670
including a handler,
exists behind the scenes.

413
00:26:06,736 --> 00:26:09,172
Mizusawa likely participated
in the robbery itself,

414
00:26:09,239 --> 00:26:11,641
then ran off with the gold.

415
00:26:12,208 --> 00:26:13,810
So Togo, the man stalking her,

416
00:26:13,877 --> 00:26:16,813
was one of the other three robbers,
or perhaps the handler?

417
00:26:18,915 --> 00:26:22,385
Did he set the fire in retaliation
because he couldn't find the gold?

418
00:26:22,452 --> 00:26:26,589
We will cooperate with Akita police
and pursue Togo as a person of interest.

419
00:26:26,656 --> 00:26:28,091
-Yes.
-Yes!

420
00:26:28,158 --> 00:26:30,860
HARUKO ASHIKAGA: CAN WE MEET UP?

421
00:26:34,230 --> 00:26:36,266
Tagusari! Come here for a second.

422
00:26:36,766 --> 00:26:39,269
Maybe because of
your solo investigation again.

423
00:26:39,335 --> 00:26:40,870
Honestly, what a pain.

424
00:26:40,937 --> 00:26:43,339
The "again" part makes it hard to defend.

425
00:26:43,406 --> 00:26:45,241
Just go and get chewed out.

426
00:26:47,510 --> 00:26:48,344
Kudo.

427
00:27:00,523 --> 00:27:01,424
Yes?

428
00:27:01,491 --> 00:27:02,492
Where is Makoto?

429
00:27:02,559 --> 00:27:05,795
He is currently being detained
and lectured.

430
00:27:05,862 --> 00:27:06,963
Oh, I see.

431
00:27:08,665 --> 00:27:09,833
Right…

432
00:27:12,068 --> 00:27:12,902
Here.

433
00:27:13,536 --> 00:27:16,106
-List of people named Togo.
-Thank you.

434
00:27:16,172 --> 00:27:18,975
There were several with that name
in the prefecture,

435
00:27:19,042 --> 00:27:21,578
but they were all either in prison
or overseas.

436
00:27:21,644 --> 00:27:23,046
All dead ends.

437
00:27:23,780 --> 00:27:25,782
You've already investigated that much?

438
00:27:26,349 --> 00:27:29,953
Those gold bars
were from the Akita robbery, right?

439
00:27:30,987 --> 00:27:32,188
How do you know that?

440
00:27:32,255 --> 00:27:34,924
I have friends who work as reporters.

441
00:27:35,558 --> 00:27:40,063
One of the robbers had a tattoo,
and Aiko Mizusawa was also a member.

442
00:27:41,965 --> 00:27:44,968
Oh, it's here! Got one!

443
00:27:45,034 --> 00:27:45,969
Amazing!

444
00:27:46,035 --> 00:27:47,170
Come on.

445
00:27:50,340 --> 00:27:53,576
My dad was a fisherman,
I used to help him often.

446
00:27:55,145 --> 00:27:56,112
Okay.

447
00:27:58,381 --> 00:27:59,449
Want to try?

448
00:27:59,516 --> 00:28:02,218
Oh… I'm a professional at the eating part.

449
00:28:02,786 --> 00:28:05,188
Oh, you must've been raised well.

450
00:28:09,626 --> 00:28:12,762
MOM

451
00:28:16,666 --> 00:28:17,734
To be honest,

452
00:28:18,535 --> 00:28:20,904
my parents never took me to the sea.

453
00:28:23,606 --> 00:28:24,607
Is that so?

454
00:28:26,176 --> 00:28:27,076
Well…

455
00:28:27,710 --> 00:28:29,646
What's your relationship with
Mr. Tagusari?

456
00:28:31,614 --> 00:28:33,650
We used to live in the same neighborhood.

457
00:28:33,716 --> 00:28:36,019
You could say we go way back.

458
00:28:37,287 --> 00:28:39,823
So that's why
you're helping him investigate?

459
00:28:43,426 --> 00:28:44,260
What?

460
00:28:45,094 --> 00:28:45,962
What?

461
00:28:47,530 --> 00:28:48,598
Nothing.

462
00:28:51,534 --> 00:28:54,103
We don't even know his face.
No way to look for him.

463
00:28:54,637 --> 00:28:57,440
Besides, Togo is probably from Akita.

464
00:28:57,507 --> 00:28:58,575
Oh, thanks.

465
00:28:58,641 --> 00:29:00,944
Want one, Mr. Tagusari?

466
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:04,681
This…

467
00:29:06,249 --> 00:29:08,251
This isn't a tattoo, it's a birthmark.

468
00:29:08,318 --> 00:29:09,519
A birthmark?

469
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:12,055
Makes sense.

470
00:29:12,555 --> 00:29:13,957
The position is the same.

471
00:29:14,490 --> 00:29:18,228
So one of the robbers
was at the scene of the arson?

472
00:29:18,294 --> 00:29:20,463
That man is the arsonist…

473
00:29:21,030 --> 00:29:22,332
It might be Togo.

474
00:29:23,032 --> 00:29:24,567
This case is going to be a relay.

475
00:29:24,634 --> 00:29:28,571
First, we need all CCTV and dashcam data
from near the apartment.

476
00:29:28,638 --> 00:29:29,706
All right, let's go.

477
00:29:29,772 --> 00:29:30,940
-Yes!
-Okay.

478
00:29:31,007 --> 00:29:32,075
-My ramen…
-Let's go.

479
00:29:32,575 --> 00:29:34,244
-You can eat it later!
-But…

480
00:29:34,310 --> 00:29:36,145
Please watch my ramen for me.

481
00:29:38,748 --> 00:29:40,783
Sorry to bother you.

482
00:29:40,850 --> 00:29:42,619
I'm from the Aoi Station.

483
00:29:43,553 --> 00:29:45,622
I would like to ask a few questions.

484
00:29:51,995 --> 00:29:52,996
Hello?

485
00:29:53,062 --> 00:29:54,898
Makoto, can we talk now?

486
00:29:54,964 --> 00:29:55,932
Sure.

487
00:29:56,966 --> 00:29:58,668
The hospital called.

488
00:30:00,036 --> 00:30:00,937
And Tsuda?

489
00:30:01,437 --> 00:30:02,505
He just woke up.

490
00:30:04,574 --> 00:30:07,110
They said we'll be able to visit
once he's stable.

491
00:30:07,176 --> 00:30:08,311
Okay.

492
00:30:08,378 --> 00:30:09,879
Once he can talk, let's go and see him.

493
00:30:09,946 --> 00:30:11,848
Sorry, I have an autopsy now.

494
00:30:14,183 --> 00:30:17,153
Mr. Tagusari. Let's go get CCTV footage
on the east side too.

495
00:30:17,687 --> 00:30:18,688
Right.

496
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:26,095
Mr. Koike, let's go.

497
00:30:26,162 --> 00:30:27,096
Okay.

498
00:30:28,431 --> 00:30:29,332
Here's more.

499
00:30:30,934 --> 00:30:33,303
You can't even see
a neck birthmark in this.

500
00:30:35,038 --> 00:30:36,873
My back is going to explode.

501
00:30:38,007 --> 00:30:40,310
Relay investigations
are a race against time.

502
00:30:40,376 --> 00:30:42,312
If the footage is overwritten, it's over.

503
00:30:42,378 --> 00:30:44,948
I know that, but still. There's so much…

504
00:30:45,448 --> 00:30:48,785
The investigation division
will help starting tomorrow.

505
00:30:48,851 --> 00:30:51,321
They are experts in analysis, after all.

506
00:30:52,855 --> 00:30:54,657
Give it here. Come on.

507
00:30:55,224 --> 00:30:56,225
What?

508
00:30:56,292 --> 00:30:57,860
What's wrong, Mr. Tagusari?

509
00:30:58,394 --> 00:31:01,030
Usually, he'll complain
about how much of a pain it is.

510
00:31:01,097 --> 00:31:03,032
I just want to finish this and go home.

511
00:31:09,038 --> 00:31:12,542
The initial examination is finished.
We found no traces of foul play.

512
00:31:12,608 --> 00:31:13,443
Yes.

513
00:31:13,509 --> 00:31:14,577
Excuse me.

514
00:31:15,912 --> 00:31:17,413
Hello.

515
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:18,314
Yes?

516
00:31:18,381 --> 00:31:19,983
Did you have an autopsy here?

517
00:31:20,049 --> 00:31:21,551
I finished just now.

518
00:31:22,051 --> 00:31:25,755
-Stocking up on food?
-Yes. Looks like we're not finishing soon.

519
00:31:26,990 --> 00:31:29,225
Is Makoto doing his job properly?

520
00:31:29,292 --> 00:31:30,727
He's not slacking off, is he?

521
00:31:32,595 --> 00:31:34,764
I wonder if something good
happened to him.

522
00:31:35,331 --> 00:31:38,167
He's working hard,
saying he wants to finish quickly.

523
00:31:39,469 --> 00:31:40,370
Is that so?

524
00:31:41,571 --> 00:31:43,506
I'm going back to the prefectural HQ.

525
00:31:44,007 --> 00:31:45,408
Must be tough working late.

526
00:31:45,975 --> 00:31:47,143
Same for you.

527
00:31:48,111 --> 00:31:49,712
But I'm counting on you.

528
00:31:50,913 --> 00:31:53,249
If the medical examiner
makes a wrong judgment,

529
00:31:53,316 --> 00:31:55,551
a crime might be overlooked.

530
00:31:56,486 --> 00:31:59,722
From the victim's perspective,
you're the last line of defense.

531
00:32:00,223 --> 00:32:01,124
So…

532
00:32:03,926 --> 00:32:05,128
I'm pretty cool, huh.

533
00:32:05,995 --> 00:32:07,463
Tooting your own horn now?

534
00:32:08,965 --> 00:32:11,901
It's not a job someone like me
should be doing.

535
00:32:32,355 --> 00:32:37,326
CONFERENCE ROOM

536
00:32:41,464 --> 00:32:42,732
Excuse me.

537
00:32:44,033 --> 00:32:45,601
Are you a family member?

538
00:32:49,539 --> 00:32:51,507
Do you know his name or anything?

539
00:32:52,642 --> 00:32:53,910
He's an acquaintance.

540
00:32:53,976 --> 00:32:55,778
-Oh, I see.
-Sorry.

541
00:32:55,845 --> 00:32:57,080
Excuse me.

542
00:32:58,714 --> 00:33:00,817
What did you come here for?

543
00:33:00,883 --> 00:33:01,851
Sorry.

544
00:33:02,351 --> 00:33:04,120
I got worried after all.

545
00:33:11,661 --> 00:33:12,728
This man…

546
00:33:15,298 --> 00:33:17,433
I thought we might be able to talk a bit,

547
00:33:18,167 --> 00:33:19,769
but he seems to still be asleep.

548
00:33:20,770 --> 00:33:24,107
Once you hear
about that incident from Tsuda…

549
00:33:26,609 --> 00:33:27,477
After that,

550
00:33:28,277 --> 00:33:29,245
what will you…

551
00:33:30,646 --> 00:33:32,381
do with him?

552
00:33:33,015 --> 00:33:34,550
I think you already know.

553
00:33:36,652 --> 00:33:37,553
Minoru?

554
00:33:49,799 --> 00:33:50,700
However…

555
00:33:53,636 --> 00:33:54,871
I'll be the one to do it.

556
00:33:56,472 --> 00:33:57,306
What?

557
00:33:58,674 --> 00:33:59,942
Since that incident,

558
00:34:01,043 --> 00:34:03,279
Makoto has been carrying everything.

559
00:34:05,715 --> 00:34:10,319
Even me, back when I couldn't do anything
and started avoiding people.

560
00:34:14,423 --> 00:34:15,491
That's why,

561
00:34:19,295 --> 00:34:21,264
I will carry him at the end.

562
00:34:25,735 --> 00:34:27,036
Don't tell Makoto.

563
00:34:27,103 --> 00:34:28,371
I won't.

564
00:34:31,107 --> 00:34:32,575
I won't tell him, but…

565
00:34:36,212 --> 00:34:37,246
Minoru?

566
00:34:38,414 --> 00:34:39,916
Are you really okay with this?

567
00:34:42,552 --> 00:34:47,290
You won't be able to do the things
you actually want to do anymore!

568
00:34:51,827 --> 00:34:53,095
I would have loved to…

569
00:34:54,197 --> 00:34:56,566
graduate from medical school
and be a forensic scientist.

570
00:34:59,168 --> 00:35:00,136
But…

571
00:35:02,004 --> 00:35:03,472
on the day of the accident,

572
00:35:05,942 --> 00:35:07,910
I threw all of that away.

573
00:35:18,421 --> 00:35:22,858
He's currently sleeping under medication,
but he might be able to talk tomorrow.

574
00:35:24,327 --> 00:35:25,394
Tomorrow?

575
00:35:27,396 --> 00:35:28,397
I understand.

576
00:35:38,174 --> 00:35:39,075
Shall we go?

577
00:35:39,976 --> 00:35:41,711
Time to open your shop, Mogi.

578
00:36:19,282 --> 00:36:20,983
Any word from the hospital?

579
00:36:21,851 --> 00:36:23,419
Tsuda still can't talk?

580
00:36:25,321 --> 00:36:30,226
He's currently sleeping under medication,
but he might be able to talk tomorrow.

581
00:36:32,395 --> 00:36:35,865
They said it will take
two or three days until he's stable.

582
00:36:38,701 --> 00:36:39,635
I see.

583
00:36:40,536 --> 00:36:41,570
And on your end?

584
00:36:43,906 --> 00:36:46,175
Tomorrow will be another day
of checking footage.

585
00:36:51,614 --> 00:36:53,115
You'll go back to the station?

586
00:36:53,182 --> 00:36:55,284
Just let me be already.

587
00:36:59,121 --> 00:37:00,289
I'll have a drink too.

588
00:37:01,891 --> 00:37:03,059
Don't push yourself.

589
00:37:05,695 --> 00:37:06,929
Want a snack?

590
00:37:07,730 --> 00:37:09,165
I'll cook something.

591
00:37:09,732 --> 00:37:10,800
Well…

592
00:37:11,567 --> 00:37:12,802
Then, hayashi rice.

593
00:37:13,302 --> 00:37:14,804
That's not exactly a snack.

594
00:37:15,371 --> 00:37:17,506
Mom never really made this
for us, did she?

595
00:37:18,674 --> 00:37:19,608
That's because

596
00:37:20,876 --> 00:37:23,279
we kept saying her cooking sucks.

597
00:37:25,214 --> 00:37:27,550
She wasn't good at cooking to begin with,

598
00:37:28,317 --> 00:37:31,020
so she practiced while working
at Mogi's place.

599
00:37:31,921 --> 00:37:34,924
The food at our house was Chinese
almost every day.

600
00:37:35,558 --> 00:37:36,659
Thanks to that,

601
00:37:37,927 --> 00:37:40,096
Mogi's shop's taste is the taste of home.

602
00:37:41,063 --> 00:37:42,498
You're using that again?

603
00:37:42,565 --> 00:37:44,467
It's delicious!

604
00:37:44,533 --> 00:37:46,202
You guys want to try some?

605
00:37:46,268 --> 00:37:47,136
No!

606
00:37:47,203 --> 00:37:49,638
-Let me put it on for you! Hey!
-No!

607
00:37:49,705 --> 00:37:51,741
1995, APRIL 26

608
00:38:00,015 --> 00:38:02,385
Makoto, you should learn
to cook a little too.

609
00:38:02,451 --> 00:38:03,319
Why?

610
00:38:06,222 --> 00:38:08,557
You'll ruin your health
if you only eat out.

611
00:38:09,592 --> 00:38:11,627
I'll be fine, as long as you are here.

612
00:38:26,242 --> 00:38:27,743
This was in Mizusawa's house too.

613
00:38:30,746 --> 00:38:33,549
I guess all houses in Kanagawa
got a flyer like that.

614
00:38:33,616 --> 00:38:34,984
No, but the numbers…

615
00:38:35,050 --> 00:38:36,185
FITNESS GYM
8,000 YEN A MONTH

616
00:38:37,486 --> 00:38:39,422
The monthly price was different.

617
00:38:39,488 --> 00:38:40,623
5,000 YEN A MONTH

618
00:38:42,725 --> 00:38:44,427
Yes, it was a lot of trouble.

619
00:38:44,994 --> 00:38:46,729
We suddenly had to stop everything.

620
00:38:47,763 --> 00:38:49,565
What about the misprinted flyers?

621
00:38:50,132 --> 00:38:51,000
Well…

622
00:38:51,901 --> 00:38:56,038
We had already finished delivering
flyers here. So we just sent out a notice.

623
00:39:24,934 --> 00:39:25,868
Hello?

624
00:39:43,986 --> 00:39:45,321
Yes, management office.

625
00:39:46,021 --> 00:39:49,325
I'm Tagusari, from the Aoi Station.
Can we speak for a moment?

626
00:39:53,295 --> 00:39:54,497
Please open up!

627
00:40:43,012 --> 00:40:44,246
Can you wait until later?

628
00:40:45,781 --> 00:40:47,016
Tsuda is dead.

629
00:41:04,466 --> 00:41:05,301
Minoru.

630
00:41:08,938 --> 00:41:09,805
Minoru.

631
00:41:10,306 --> 00:41:11,473
Did Tsuda say anything?

632
00:41:21,917 --> 00:41:22,918
Don't screw with me.

633
00:41:28,223 --> 00:41:30,459
Why did you just go and die on your own?

634
00:41:35,464 --> 00:41:38,667
If you're going to die,
tell us everything first.

635
00:41:42,304 --> 00:41:45,107
What were the two of us even doing
for over 30 years?

636
00:42:09,198 --> 00:42:12,501
The clothes and personal effects
from when Mr. Tsuda was brought in.

637
00:42:17,339 --> 00:42:18,407
Excuse me.

638
00:42:26,515 --> 00:42:28,050
What are you doing?

639
00:42:28,117 --> 00:42:31,387
Someone related to him
might know something.

640
00:42:31,954 --> 00:42:33,489
There must be a clue somewhere.

641
00:42:57,179 --> 00:42:58,747
Is it a phone number?

642
00:43:15,931 --> 00:43:16,965
Hello.

643
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:19,501
Who is this?

644
00:43:37,252 --> 00:43:38,287
Hello?

645
00:43:53,035 --> 00:43:55,137
You know a man
named Yuji Tsuda, don't you?

646
00:43:55,204 --> 00:43:56,805
Maybe we should've left them alone.

647
00:43:56,872 --> 00:43:59,274
You mean there's another culprit
besides Tsuda?

648
00:43:59,842 --> 00:44:01,577
Is that key the only clue left?

649
00:44:01,643 --> 00:44:02,644
No way…

650
00:44:02,711 --> 00:44:03,946
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.
